This Job executes the hping command to send custom TCP (e.g. SYN TCP) packets (like ping does with ICMP) and measures the rtt delay of the stream of packets (with a frequency of count packets). It sends syslog in case of error.

Required Arguments:
  - dest : the destination IP address

Optionnal Arguments:
  - rtt : The Round trip time of tcp connection (SYN)

Example:
  - Ping 172.20.0.83 : -a "destination_ip 172.20.0.83"
  - Ping 172.20.0.83 with packets of size 100 bytes : -a "destination_ip 172.20.0.83" "packetsize 100"

